You won't be let into the class. I don't even know if a time conflict override will work, because you're on the waitlist, not enrolled.

Although some sections just opened up as they processed the waitlist, try enrolling directly into those!

In case the sections are full by the time you see this and are also in CS 162, I let Raluca know of the situation and she requested that the registrar open up a section that doesn't conflict with 162. Not a high chance, but it's possible!

The current schedule of 161 is final.

Of the 68 students on the 161 waitlist now only 1 is on the 162 waitlist and 11 are enrolled in 162.  That's less than 20% of the waitlist and those students will be aided by others who get out of their way by moving to the new section.

Students who have conflicts with the new discussion sections should not add themselves to those waitlists as SIS will indeed block enrollment.

I just enrolled in Section 111 for CS 16. Even though there's no one in the class, I was still added to the waitlist. The discussion section time also conflicts with one of my other classes, and I was planning on overriding the conflict. However, no override notification showed up in Calcentral when I was added to the waitlist. Will a conflict notification only show up when the waitlist is processed, and will I be prevented from joining the class until I request a time conflict override?
